    "date": "2017-09-15",
    "comment": "Rationale: tagged versions of GLUT4 are shown to translocate to the presynaptic plasma membrane during electrical activity. Preventing this from happening (by genetic ablation of GLUT4) blocks synaptic vesicle endocytosis in a way that is almost identical to simply removing extracellular glucose. The defect in vesicle endocytosis can be rescued by re-expressing intact GLUT4 in the KD neurons but not by re-expressing a mutant GLUT4 that can not transport glucose. Experimental description: Hippocampal CA1-CA3 neurons were isolated from 1- to 3-day-old rats of mixed gender",
